This cover point covers the possible values of PWRITE signal. There are two bins of corresponding values [APB3_READ] and [APB3_WRITE]
Both PENABLE and PREADY asserted simultaneously after the PSELx assertion. Cover point xfer_without_wait contains the bin of value [TRUE]

PREADY will assert after few clock cycle delay of the PENABLE signal asserted. Cover point xfer_with_wait contains the four different bins of the corresponding values [1]:MAX_UINT]. ''1â : means HREADY asserted one cycle after the PENABLE. ''2â : means HREADY asserted two cycle after the PENABLE. and similarly for others bins.
Two types of write transfer are described in this section: â¢ With no wait states â¢ With wait states.
This cover point covers the write transfer without any wait state. Cross cover point xfer_without_wait with xfer_type covers it.

This cover point covers the write transfer with number of wait state. PREADY will assert after few clock cycle delay of the PENABLE signal asserted. Cross cover point xfer_with_wait with xfer_type covers it.
Two types of read transfer are described in this section: â¢ With no wait states â¢ With wait states.
